Photo: Robin Jerstad, Express-News File Photo Image 55 of 55 San Antonio Scorpions’ Soto suspended while being investigated for leaking tactics to opposing teams 1 / 55 Back to Gallery Scorpions midfielder Josue Soto has been suspended from all team activities for allegedly providing opposing teams with strategic information, multiple sources confirmed to the Express-News.
According to a release from the NASL, which confirmed his suspension Friday afternoon, the league office has begun an investigation into Soto’s “potential misconduct.”
Scorpions manager Alen Marcina declined comment at Friday’s practice. Team president Howard Cornfield was said to be traveling, and not available for comment.
The extent of Soto’s alleged misconduct was not immediately clear. Sources characterized it as sharing of information, such as starting lineups, with former teammates. It is unclear whether there was any intent to sabotage the Scorpions.
Soto, 26, played for the Scorpions during their inaugural season in 2012, scoring two goals in 25 games while on loan from Major League Soccer ’s Houston Dynamo .
He returned in 2014 after a brief stint with now-defunct Chivas USA , and has no goals or assists in 14 appearances this season.
